<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 21 at 9:04PM CDT until July 22 at 12:00AM CDT by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 930 PM CDT
FOR NORTH CENTRAL PIKE AND SOUTHERN BULLOCK COUNTIES...
At 904 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Midway to near Linwood, moving southeast at 20
mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Pickett, Linwood, Aberfoil, Beans Crossroads and Perote.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
